Package com.company

Class Phone

java.lang.Object
com.company.Phone
public class Phone
extends java.lang.Object
Class Phone stores data about phones and allows to simulate their behaviour.

  • Method Details

    • call

      public void call​(Phone phone, boolean accept, java.time.Duration conversationTime)
      Method that simulates phone calls and stores information about them in phone register. Depending on phone state it behaves differently.
      Parameters:
      phone - Destination phone object to be called.
      accept - Flag indicating if destination phone should accept call.
      conversationTime - Value of this parameter is used when accept flag is true. It tells how long the conversation will be.

    • receiveCall

      private void receiveCall​(Phone from, boolean accept, java.time.Duration conversationTime) throws CallRejectedException
      Method invoked by call when both phones are available and are ready to connect. It simulates conversations between phones which will be unavailable during connection for other phones.
      Parameters:
      from - Source phone object that is calling.
      accept - Flag indicates if destination phone should accept call.
      conversationTime - Passed through call method. Tells how long both phones will be unavailable.
      Throws:
      CallRejectedException - If flag accept is false.

      fileName - File name with extension.
